benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01 (valid with no params), TC02 (objectType filter), TC03/TC04 (audit values), TC05 (combined objectType and audit), TC06 (no custom fields -> empty array), TC07 (no matches for objectType), TC08 (all enum objectType values), TC09 (audit enum values), TC11 (large dataset performance), TC14/TC15 (auth errors), TC16 (service unavailable), TC17 (SQL injection-like input), TC18 (XSS attempt), TC19/TC20 (timeouts/retries), TC21 (regression - audit handling), TC22 (backward compatibility), TC23 (integration - audit service down), TC24 (data consistency), TC25/TC26 (performance under load), TC27 (state variation: mixed accounts), TC28 (degraded performance with logging), TC29/TC30 (min/max edge cases), TC31 (partial input), TC32 (invalid parameter type), TC33/TC34/TC35/TC36 (extreme/edge accountId/objectType inputs), TC37/TC38 (accessibility and descriptive errors), TC39 (recovery from error): Coverage of various valid/invalid inputs, error handling, and recovery scenarios.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets or explicit page/size parameters.
Authorization: No explicit test for 403 Forbidden (only 401 unauthorized scenarios).
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching validation.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulating rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Server-side validation for some edge invalid inputs beyond accountId/objectType (e.g., extremely long strings for other parameters) is not explicitly covered.
Database/Internal error scenarios beyond service unavailability (e.g., 500 from DB) are not explicitly tested.
Granular correctness checks for schema conformance across all object permutations are implied but not enumerated for every TC (e.g., TC08/tailored schema checks across all enum values).
recommendations: Add pagination tests to exercise page and pageSize parameters and verify correct paging, total counts, and performance on large result sets.
Add explicit 403 Forbidden scenario to verify proper authorization handling for authenticated-but-not-permitted users.
Introduce tests for caching behavior to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and cache validation logic.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API gracefully handles bursts of requests and respects configured quotas.
Expand edge-case input validation tests to cover additional extreme inputs (e.g., very long strings in other query params) and ensure proper 400 responses.
Include tests for deeper server-side failure modes (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error from database or dependent services) to verify error handling and observability.
Add targeted tests to confirm schema conformance for all combinations of objectType and audit values, ensuring full parity with the defined CustomField schema across scenarios.
